According to Greenberger & Padesky (2016), thinking is quite different in #depression and #anxiety 

Depressed thinking tends to be negative, hopeless, and self-critical.

Anxious thoughts tend to be catastrophic and worry about specific future events, as well as general worry.

Seeing a lot of posts that appear to assume that SSRIs are the only drugs prescribed for #depression.

Seeing a lot of posts that appear to assume that SSRIs are the only drugs prescribed for #depression.

For the record, they are just one in a range of anti-depressant medication types. I personally use a tetracyclic NaSSa that doesn't affect the reuptake of serotonin at all.
